snippet.textDisplay: I brought this up in the other video and I will again bring it up here. Naruto exploding all his chakra INCLUDED all the chakra he uses in the KCM and KCM2 mode. He was in base yes but the energy released was ALL of the chakra inside him, "his" chakra has always, since day 1, included the Fox inside him. Numerous times the series has specifically said all of Naruto's chakra is gone and he is running totally on the fox. Basically to say the explosion was caused by base Naruto is kind of misleading since the bomb was based on nothing but his maximum chakra which does not actually change between modes. Base Naruto has the exact same amount of chakra as KCM2 six paths amped Naruto.

snippet.textDisplay:
Low key though the math was all over the place.

Assuming that because All Might said his punches were 60x stronger during his prime doesn’t justify a flat out x60 multiplier to every single feat we’ve seen post injury.

Not to mention Guys power measurement came from the fact that base form naturo blew up most of the moon and we saw Guy was stronger than base form naturo so tHaTs a sUpEr SmArT wAy To CaLcUlAtE. This doesn’t take into consideration HOW the chakra was used. There are too many factors and unknown variables for this to be a good method of measurement.

Oh and if both fighters die as a result of the fight then it’s a draw. One might die shortly before the other but the end result is them killing each other and that sounds like a draw to me.

Guys,

Love the series, I'm a long time fan. I started watching just before the first Goku vs. superman. Although I don't agree with the outcome of either of those fights..i been watching for a few years and have noticed the changes you guys have made to the show over the years. I have to say boomstick is one of, if not the CRINGIEST, ANNOYING, and UNNECESSARY cohosts of all time.

PlEASE TONE DOWN BOOMSTICKS CORNY JOKES AND HIS OVERALL LINES

In my opinion the character is mad annoying, and adds nothing to the videos other than extra time.
He was a bit toned down in the beginning, and he was much better in that role.

Thanks for the years of entertainment and interesting conversation starters, hope you take this critiscism constructively.
